benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/tags - Add tags to invoice item

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC05, @TC13, @TC20, @TC22, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25 cover successful addition of tags with valid data.

Invalid Payload: @TC06 (missing header), @TC07 (invalid invoice item id), @TC08 (non-existent invoice item), @TC09 (malformed JSON), @TC10 (empty list), @TC11 (invalid tag UUID), @TC12 (unsupported parameters), @TC13 (duplicate UUIDs), @TC24 (null or empty strings), @TC25 (timeout) cover various invalid input scenarios.

Server Error Handling: @TC08 (not found), @TC09 (malformed JSON), @TC11 (invalid UUID), @TC12 (unsupported parameters), @TC17 (service unavailable), @TC21 (dependency down), @TC25 (timeout) cover server and dependency errors.
State Variation: @TC22 (partial data), @TC23 (max tags), @TC20 (existing tags) cover different database states.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with pagination.
Authorization: No explicit tests for unauthorized access beyond missing header (@TC06) and invalid token scenarios (@TC16).
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests to verify rate limiting or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Performance under load: Only @TC14 mentions performance under heavy load, but lacks detailed load testing scenarios.
Soft Deletes or concurrency issues beyond race conditions are not explicitly tested.
recommendations: Add explicit tests for pagination handling when retrieving large sets of tags.
Include tests for authorization with invalid or expired tokens to ensure proper access control.
Implement rate limiting tests to verify system stability under high request volumes.
Add scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behaviors.
Include performance testing scenarios for high load and stress conditions.
Test soft delete behaviors and concurrency issues for race conditions.
